                    <item xml:id="a6">
                    <desc>
                    <locus target="#152v" facs="155"> f. 152v, bottom</locus>
                    Concluding Prayer after the recitation of the Psalter, in blue ink in an untrained hand.
                    <foreign xml:lang="gez">ስብሐት ለአብ ወወልድ ወመንፈስ ቅዱስ ለአለም ወለአለመ አለም ሰአሊ ለነ ቅድስት ማርያም ምህረተ ክርስቶስ ወልድከ (sic) የሀውጸነ ማርያም ሰአል ለነ ዳዊት ቅድመ መንበሩ ለጸባኦት አምላከ ዳዊት ተዘከረነ ወአምላከ ዳዊት ተሣሃለነ አድህነኒ እምእለት እኪት ወባልሀነ እምኵሉ መንሱት<gap reason="omitted"/></foreign>
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="e3">
                    <desc>
                    marginal notation throughout
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="e4">
                    <desc>
                      words of text are written interlinearly (<locus target="#1r #8v #11r #11v #12r" facs="003 011 013 014"/>, etc.);
                      lines of text are written interlinearly (<locus target="#14r #23v #26v #32v" facs="016 025 029 035"/>, etc.);
                      lines of text are written in the upper margin with a symbol (┴) marking the location where the text is to be inserted (<locus target="#60r" facs="062"> f. 60r, line 5</locus>);
                      erasure markings are visible (<locus target="#7v #40r #66v #74r #77v #96r #116v" facs="010 042 069 076 080 098 119"/>, etc.);
                      text has been removed (e.g., <locus target="#5r #59r" facs="007 061"/>)
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="e5">
                    <desc>
                    <locus target="#20v" facs="023"> f. 20v, line 3</locus> lines have been drawn above and below text to signal its erasure to correct homoeoteleuton
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="a">
                    <desc>
                    The scribe regularly has to complete a line of text on another line. Much of the problem is addressed through the selection of an appropriate aspect ratio for the codex combined with an appropriate script size. But, where the line of text is still too long, the scribe completes the line of text above or below the end of the line (throughout). This scribe also will reduce the font size at the end of lines to avoid having to go onto the next line (e.g., <locus target="#15v #18r #18v" facs="018 020 021"/>)
                    </desc>
                    </item>
